&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
"We put attention on certain rules of behavior, but this does not mean to make magistrates subjects that must be in a shadow zone, in forced silence. The magistrates can and must participate in the public discussion, but must do so with the style and profile of the magistrate," he added.
&nbsp;
< blockquote
"The justice machine is still slow, but it recovers, even quickly, greater efficiency. The Minister said so in his report to the Chambers on the state of justice. We have significant percentages of reduction of arrears and process times. Therefore I look to the future with cautious optimism." &nbsp;
</blockquote
&nbsp;
"We wanted this congress - he explains - in the light of many months of criticism to the judiciary to make a serious reflection, to take seriously the criticisms received, even when they were entrusted to media messages with rates of defensivity regarding the individual magistrates. I believe that we will approve a motion for a united hope, reaffirming that the interpretation of the law cannot, that the subjugation to the law is not in question and that the magistrates, having as interpreters of the law a wide margin of discretion, must take charge to protect also the image of impartiality when they intervene in social life and of relationship".
